==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lariat
<hw>Lar"i*at</hw> <pr>(l⟦acr⟧r"⟦icr⟧*⟦acr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Sp. <ets>la reata</ets> the rope; <ets>la</ets> the +
<ets>reata</ets> rope. Cf. <er>Reata</er>.]</ety> <def>A long, slender
rope made of hemp or strips of hide, esp. one with a noose; -- used as a
lasso for catching cattle, horses, etc., and for picketing a horse so
that he can graze without wandering.</def> <mark>[Mexico & Western
U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 831 --></p>

<p><ent>Lariat</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Lariat
<hw>Lar"i*at</hw> <pr>(l⟦acr⟧r"⟦icr⟧*⟦acr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Lariated</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Lariating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To secure with a
lariat fastened to a stake, as a horse or mule for grazing; also, to
lasso or catch with a lariat.</def> <mark>[Western U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Laridae</ent>⟦br⟧
